Class PrimitiveArray

  • Direct Known Subclasses:

    public abstract class PrimitiveArray
extends org.ObjectLayout.intrinsifiable.AbstractArray
    A abstract base class for subclassable primitive and reference arrays. Subclassable arrays are useful for modeling the commonly used "struct with variable array at the end" available in the C family of languages. JDKs may optimize the layout of a PrimitiveArray such that access to the array members may be faster than regular de-referenced access through a nested array reference.
